// Documentation of a feature that isn't part of the safety-certified surface.
// The safety manual omits it; every other site reads as if the tag weren't
// there, since the distinction only means something to Slint SC users.
//
// The specification chapters are synced into the safety manual verbatim, so
// both sites import this from the same path and the component has to tell
// them apart itself: the safety manual sets SLINT_SC_SAFETY_MANUAL in its
// dev and build scripts.
//
// A paragraph in here states no requirement, so it carries no `{#sls.…}`
// identifier -- see rehype-sls-ids.mjs, which exempts it from the
// completeness check, and traceability.rs, which skips the region when it
// scans for anchors.
const omit = process.env.SLINT_SC_SAFETY_MANUAL === "1";
---

{!omit && <slot />}
